Hooks:
You can call hook_add(<hook name>, ...) to have your function called when one of the following
events occurs:
    send 
    preinput 
    loselink 
    prompt 
    userinput 
    postoutput 
    output 
    done 
    keypress 
    connect 
    command

Dirt commands:
You can access dirt commands (/print, /send, etc) by calling them with "dirt" prefixed:
    dirt_print, dirt_send, etc.
